rails 6 project using a gem

$ rvm install ruby-2.6.2

$ ruby -v                                                                             

ruby 2.6.2p47 (2019-03-13 revision 67232) [x86_64-darwin18]

$ gem -v
3.0.3

$ gem update --system

$ rvm gemset list

$ rvm gemset use global

$ gem list

$ gem outdated

$ gem update

$ echo "gem: --no-document" >> ~/.gemrc

$ gem install bundler

$ gem install nokogiri

Install Rails
make a gemset for the beta release:
$ rvm use ruby-2.6.2@rails6.0.0.beta3 --create

$ gem install rails --version=6.0.0.beta3

$ rails -v

New Rails Application
Hereâ€™s how to create a project-specific gemset, installing Rails, and creating a new application.

$ mkdir todo

$ cd todo

$ rvm use ruby-2.6.2@todo --ruby-version --create

$ gem install rails --version=6.0.0.beta3

$ rails new .

$ yarn -v 

$ yarn check

$ yarn check --integrity

$ yarn check --verify-tree

if needed:
$ brew install yarn

$ brew install redis

$ gem install foreman

$ gem 'devise', '~> 4.6', '>= 4.6.1'

$ bundle

$ rails generate devise:install

Some setup you must do manually if you haven't yet:

  1. Ensure you have defined default url options in your environments files. Here
     is an example of default_url_options appropriate for a development environment
     in config/environments/development.rb:

       config.action_mailer.default_url_options = { host: 'localhost', port: 3000 }

     In production, :host should be set to the actual host of your application.

  2. Ensure you have defined root_url to *something* in your config/routes.rb.
     For example:

       root to: "home#index"

  3. Ensure you have flash messages in app/views/layouts/application.html.erb.
     For example:

      <%= notice %>

      <%= alert %>

  4. You can copy Devise views (for customization) to your app by running:

$ rails g devise:views

$ rails db:create

$ rails generate devise User

$ rails db:migrate




